                width="400" height="400"
                loading="lazy"
                class="rounded-lg w-full"
              />
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2 text-center">Alfa Laval NX-418 Decanter in ORS Module</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Skid Mounted Crude Oil Recovery System -->
        <div id="skid" class="mb-8 border-b border-gray-100 pb-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-3">Skid Mounted Crude Oil Recovery System</h3>
          <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-3">
            The ORS is also available in a &lsquo;Skid Mounted&rsquo; design, which is suitable for fixed installation in existing facilities. We supply each of the 3-step components as an individual skid-mounted system.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
            The customer has the flexibility to configure the ORS around pre-installed tanks or other assets. Also, the skid-mounted configuration offers lower costs and shorter lead times.
          </p>
          <img
            src="/images/crude-oil-centrifuge/DMPX-042-Self-Cleaning-Disc-Stack-Centrifuge-for-Crude-Oil-Slop.jpg"
            alt="DMPX-042 Self-Cleaning Disc Stack Centrifuge for Crude Oil Slop — Skid Mounted Oil Recovery System"
            width="800" height="981"
            loading="lazy"
            class="rounded-lg max-w-md w-full mx-auto"
          />
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2 text-center">DMPX-042 Self-Cleaning Disc Stack Centrifuge for Crude Oil Slop</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Refinery Slop Oil -->
        <div id="slop-oil" class="mb-8 border-b border-gray-100 pb-8">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-3">Refinery Slop Oil</h3>
          <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-3">
            Oil refinery waste streams are also known as refinery slop. This waste stream consists of wastewater, crude oil, and sludge. It often contains varying amounts of oil emulsions as well.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-3">
            A refinery slop treatment system includes a crude oil decanter for de-sludging. A high-speed disc stack centrifuge separates the liquid phases in the de-sludged oil. Using chemicals helps the centrifuge break the oily-water mix if the emulsion is present.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[#2D2D2D]">
            Therefore, both the decanter and disc stack centrifuge are well suited for refinery slop oil treatment.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Water Washing -->
        <div id="water-washing">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-3">Water Washing</h3>
          <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-3">
            Heavy metals, such as lead, iron, arsenic, nickel, etc., are present in crude oil. Though their presence in trace levels is not an issue, higher levels of metals can cause a problem for the producer.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-3">
            Oil companies do not want to buy crude oil with heavy metals beyond their specified level.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-3">
            Certain types of crude oil are washable with water to remove heavy metals by adsorption. Water absorbs the metals and needs to be separated. A 3-phase disc stack centrifuge recovers the crude oil from the wash water.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-3">
            Of course, this process creates a stream of water with adsorbed heavy metals. This contaminated water stream needs disposal through proper means.
          </p>
          <p class="text-[#2D2D2D]">
            <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/" class="text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] font-medium">Contact Dolphin Centrifuge</a> for further information regarding the use of crude oil centrifuges. Let us use our expertise to your benefit!
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Mid-Page CTA -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-[#1B3A5C] to-[#2a4f7a] rounded-xl p-6 md:p-8 text-white mb-8">
        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center md:justify-between gap-4">
          <div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Need a Crude Oil Recovery System?</h3>
            <p class="text-blue-100">Our engineers will evaluate your crude oil application and design a containerized or skid-mounted centrifuge solution.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
            <a href="/contact-for-alfa-laval-centrifuges/" class="bg-[#E8A317] hover:bg-yellow-500 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition whitespace-nowrap">Get a Quote</a>
            <a href="tel:+12485222573" class="border border-white text-white hover:bg-white hover:text-[#1B3A5C] font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg transition whitespace-nowrap">(248) 522-2573</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Specifications -->
      <div id="specifications" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4">Specifications</h2>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The following are the specifications for a typical Alfa Laval three-phase centrifuge processing <strong>API 40 Light Crude Oil.</strong>
        </p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-[#1B3A5C] text-white">
                <th class="py-3 px-3 text-left font-semibold">Parameter</th>
                <th class="py-3 px-3 text-left font-semibold"><a href="/alfa-laval-whpx-510-centrifuge/" class="text-[#E8A317] hover:underline">Alfa Laval WHPX-510</a></th>
                <th class="py-3 px-3 text-left font-semibold"><a href="/alfa-laval-whpx-513/" class="text-[#E8A317] hover:underline">Alfa Laval WHPX-513</a></th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-200">
                <td class="py-3 px-3 font-semibold text-[#1B3A5C]">Processing Capacity</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-3 font-mono">25 GPM on Light Crude Oil</td>
                <td class="py-3 px-3 font-mono">40 GPM on Light Crude Oil</td>
